cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.MA, cs.DS, cs.SY. 

The paper focuses on developing a framework for mobility-aware routing in mobile robotic networks, which involves network infrastructure, robotics, and control theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of a mobility meta-model and routing mechanisms, which are related to robotics and machine learning, respectively. Hence, cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.MA (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The paper also mentions the optimization of routing decisions, which involves data structures (cs.DS) and system optimization (cs.SY).
